(356, 1, '2013-08-01 21:13:48', '2013-08-01 21:13:48', '<p>While many thousand people flocked to London last week to welcome the Royal Baby, Europlus Direct had the huge honour of being allowed even closer to the action.</p>\r\n<p><img class=" size-large-image wp-image-357 aligncenter" src="http://europlusdirect.localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/palace1-620x370.png" alt="palace1" width="620" height="370" /></p>\r\n<p>In conjunction with the award for the <strong>Queen’s Award for Enterprise</strong> in the category “International Trade” we were invited to a reception or winners held at Buckingham Palace and each given the opportunity to meet Her Majesty The Queen herself.</p>\r\n<p>Afterwards we got to meet many of the other winners as well as some members of the Royal Family who had come to congratulate and speak to the winners. Needless to say the day went by very, very fast, but we all thoroughly enjoyed it and are very proud to show off our latest Queens Award.</p>\r\n<p>May we take this opportunity of extending our thanks to <strong>IBM</strong> and all of our customers for your valued support and on-going commitment to <strong>Europlus Direct</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Our sister company One Global is also to be recognised for their vast expertise in delivering all our translation requirements and provision of multi-lingual staff in all our global offices (<a href="http://one-global.com/">www.one-global.com</a>).</p>', 'Europlus Direct visit Buckingham Palace to Receive Award', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'europlus-direct-visit-buckingham-palace-to-receive-award', '', '', '2015-04-21 22:53:55', '2015-04-21 22:53:55', '', 0, 'http://europlusdirect.localhost/?post_type=cpt_news&#038;p=356', 0, 'cpt_news', '', 0),
(357, 1, '2015-04-21 21:13:09', '2015-04-21 21:13:09', '', 'palace1', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'palace1', '', '', '2015-04-21 21:13:09', '2015-04-21 21:13:09', '', 356, 'http://europlusdirect.localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/palace1.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(358, 1, '2013-07-05 21:16:31', '2013-07-05 21:16:31', '<p>“Leaps of Faith” and “Total Wipeouts” – <a href="http://www.europlusdirect.com/">Europlus Direct</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.one-global.com/">One Global</a> – Team Building 2013</p>\r\n<p>Even a good team can do with getting even better, and what does the trick better than a fantastic team building day? On June 20<sup>th</sup>/21<sup>st</sup>, both companies were invited to experience team building at various locations across the dales.</p>\r\n<p>In previous years the teams here at Europlus and One global arranged a life-sized Monopoly Race for us which led us through Leeds, last year we took part in a Martial Arts class and got creative at the Salt Pots Pottery Studio.</p>\r\n<p>This year, however, was a whole different class of team building event which got us in touch with all the elements.</p>\r\n<p>First of all, we got high up in the air at the High Adventure Outdoor Education Centre in Cowling (<a href="http://highadventureoec.co.uk/">http://highadventureoec.co.uk/</a>). There we got all harnessed up and ready to climb some of their outdoor facilities such as “Jacob’s Ladder”, a huge vertical ladder with rungs that are further apart the higher you get, “The Gladiator Challenge”, a climbing challenge with rope ladders, revolving ladders and even tyres, and “The Leap of Faith”, a telegraph pole (this much we agreed on) with a small platform on top from which you jump into thin air to try and hold on to a metal trapeze bar suspended nearby. Scary stuff but almost everyone gave it a go!</p>\r\n<p>After replenishing our energy at lunch and to give our arms a bit of a rest, the second part of the day took us deep into Keighley Moor. We were dropped off in two separate teams, given a map, a compass and a backpack with some water, energy bars and – alarmingly – an emergency foil blanket and were told “Good Luck!”. What followed was a fantastic orienteering walk through the beautiful Keighley Moors, including sheep, reservoirs and stunning views. Let’s just say the map helped almost everyone find their way to the third part of the day. No names mentioned J!.</p>\r\n<p>The third part of our day took us to Ponden Reservoir where we (or those of us who made it) met the team from High Adventures again for a competition in raft building. Each of the teams had 4 big plastic barrels, 6 wooden poles and a whole lot of rope to build a raft that would carry all 5 team members. The results went from very professional sturdy rafts, to the more improvised kind (made with love, obviously!). It didn’t really matter in the end as almost everyone ended up in the water when rogue barrels popped out of their frames and rafts were boarded like enemy ships by opposing team members. “Bring clothes that <em>may</em> get a little wet”, they’d told us.</p>\r\n<p>When everyone got back on terra firma, some of us even used the jetty on the water as a launching pad for some pretty great dives into the reservoir.</p>\r\n<p>So everyone had a fantastic day with the elements. Climbing high in the air, long walks on firm ground, and somewhat wobbly rafts on refreshing water.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks to our very brave teams and all at High Adventure.</p>', 'Europlus Direct & One Global – Team Building 2013', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'europlus-direct-one-global-team-building-2013', '', '', '2015-04-21 21:17:27', '2015-04-21 21:17:27', '', 0, 'http://europlusdirect.localhost/?post_type=cpt_news&#038;p=358', 0, 'cpt_news', '', 0),
